  "prompt": "How are Telugu and Tamil languages related?",
  "response": "Telugu and Tamil are both Dravidian languages spoken primarily in South India, but they have some key differences:\n\n1. Language Family:\n- Both belong to the Dravidian language family\n- They are distinct languages with separate linguistic structures\n\n2. Geographic Origin:\n- Telugu is primarily spoken in Andhra Pradesh and Telangana\n- Tamil is primarily spoken in Tamil Nadu and parts of Sri Lanka\n\n3. Linguistic Similarities:\n- Share some grammatical structures\n- Have similar phonetic characteristics\n- Contain some common vocabulary roots\n- Use similar writing scripts with some variations\n\n4. Differences:\n- Different spoken and written forms\n- Distinct grammatical rules\n- Different pronunciation\n- Unique vocabulary and linguistic nuances\n\n5. Historical Relationship:\n- Both languages developed in South India\n- Influenced by Sanskrit and other regional languages\n- Evolved separately over centuries\n\nWhile Telugu and Tamil share a common linguistic heritage as Dravidian languages, they are separate languages with their own unique characteristics and are not mutually intelligible.",
